y information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778077/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Warships: Exports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many warships surplus to requirements they have sold to foreign governments in each year since 2000; what were their names; and to which governments they were sold.","false","Biography information for Lord Campbell of Pittenweem",,"Lord Campbell of Pittenweem","HL2622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778078","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-07","<p>Following Royal Assent of the Housing and Planning Act 2016, a Working Group of relevant experts was established to provide recommendations to ministers on what, if any, legislative requirements for electrical safety in the private rented sector should be introduced. The working group report has been published online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/electrical-safety-standards-in-the-private-rented-sector-working-group-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/electrical-safety-standards-in-the-private-rented-sector-working-group-report</a></p><p>The Government will engage further with the sector to test the recommendations of the working group to ensure that any regulation introduced is balanced and works for landlords and tenants.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2017-11-07T16:47:12.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778078/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778078/answer","171107 private rented sector working group report HL2623.pdf","171107 private rented sector working group report HL2623.pdf","The Working Group report","The Working Group report","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778078/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-26","Private Rented Housing: Electrical Safety","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by the Minister of State for Communities and Local Government on 3 July (HC1801), what action, if any, they plan to take following the report of the working group on mandatory electrical safety checks set up under the Housing and Planning Act 2016.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL2623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778079","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-06","<p>In 2014-15, there were 1,971,000 couple households in receipt of tax credits and 1,902,000 in 2015-16. Finalised awards data for 2016-17 is not yet available.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the number of hours worked by both partners is not readily available from the finalised annual awards data, and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2017-11-06T16:02:41.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778079/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778079/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-26","Welfare Tax Credits","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many couple households in the UK were in receipt of tax credits; and in how many of those households both partners were in paid work for at least 16 hours per week, in (1) 2014–15, (2) 2015–16, and (3) 2016–17.","false","Biography information for Baroness Sherlock",,"Baroness Sherlock","HL2624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778080","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-02","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>",,"Baroness Buscombe",,"2017-11-02T14:55:21.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778080/answer","Biography information for Baroness Buscombe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778080/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-26","Universal Credit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many couple households in the UK were in receipt of Universal Credit, and in how many of those households both partners were in paid work for at least 16 hours per week, in (1) 2014–15, (2) 2015–16, and (3) 2016–17.","false","Biography information for Baroness Sherlock",,"Baroness Sherlock","HL2625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778081","Department for Education","false","2017-11-09","<p>Various provisions of EU law underpin fees legislation on higher education, including: Article 18 of the Treaty of the Functioning of the EU (TFEU), prohibiting discrimination on the grounds of nationality; Article 21 of the TFEU, covering the right to move and reside freely within the territory of the Member States; Article 45 of the TFEU, covering freedom of movement for workers within the Union and prohibiting discrimination based on nationality between workers of the member states; the Free Movement Directive 2004/38/EC and Regulation 492/2011.</p><p>Legislation enables universities to charge students, without a specified connection with the UK, fees at a higher level than eligible students with such a connection to the UK. This differential fee charging is not unlawful discrimination under the Equality Act 2010. The Equality Act prevents universities from discriminating, including when charging fees, on the basis of protected characteristics including nationality, except where the discrimination is permitted by other legislation.</p><p>In order to qualify for home fee status and be eligible for tuition fee caps, students must have a specified connection with the UK. Eligible European Economic Area migrant workers, self-employed persons, frontier workers and frontier self-employed persons and their eligible family members who meet the residency criteria may benefit from capped fees and home fee status.</p><p> </p>",,"The Earl of Courtown","HL2627 ; HL2628","2017-11-09T15:52:44.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778081/answer","Biography information for The Earl of Courtown","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778081/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Overseas Students: Fees and Charges","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what are the governing provisions in EU law that require universities to charge EU students the same as UK students.","false","Biography information for Baroness Wolf of Dulwich",,"Baroness Wolf of Dulwich","HL2626"
