"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778126","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-16","<p>Departmental records show the following expenditure by financial year on software licenses specifically for E-Claims:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Spend (inc VAT)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>£271,200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>£43,560</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The E-Claims service is a management and control system for the delivery of programmes to meet European Commission guidelines. The public facing component of the service allows users to apply for European Regional Development Fund (ERDF) or European Social Fund (ESF) money.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-11-16T17:33:09.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778126/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778126/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778126/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-26","EU Grants and Loans: Computer Software","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 24 October 2017 to Question 107778, how much his Department spent on software licences for e-claims for (a) 2015, (b) 2016 and (c) 2017.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","109985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778127","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-02","<p>My Department has recently published estimates of the number of leasehold dwellings in England. These can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/estimating-the-number-of-leasehold-dwellings-in-england-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/estimating-the-number-of-leasehold-dwellings-in-england-2015-to-2016</a></p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-02T17:29:17.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778127/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778127/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778127/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-26","Owner Occupation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of people who own their home on a (a) freehold and (b) leasehold basis in England; and if he will make  a statement.","false","Biography information for Emma Hardy","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Emma Hardy","109976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778128","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-01","<p>The Government’s consultation, <em>Tackling unfair practices in the leasehold market</em>, considered a number of issues within the leasehold sector including the sale of new built leasehold houses, and onerous ground rents. The consultation also sought views on what further areas of leasehold reform should be prioritised and why.</p><p>The public consultation, which closed on 19 September, received around 6,000 replies. We are carefully analysing the responses, and will issue the Government's response in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-01T16:32:20.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778128/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778128/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778128/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-26","Leasehold: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to bring forward legislation to reform leasehold; and if he will make  a statement.","false","Biography information for Emma Hardy","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Emma Hardy","109977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778129","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Department does not hold this information.</p><p>The Government’s consultation, Tackling unfair practices in the leasehold market, considered a number of issues within the leasehold sector including the sale of new built leasehold houses, and onerous ground rents. The consultation also sought views on what further areas of leasehold reform should be prioritised and why.</p><p>The public consultation, which closed on 19 September, received around 6,000 replies. We are carefully analysing the responses, and will issue the Government response in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-02T17:26:51.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778129/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778129/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778129/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-26","Ground Rent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the rise in the level of ground rent for leaseholders who own their leaseholds in (a) Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle constituency and (b) England in the last 20 years; and if he will make  a statement.","false","Biography information for Emma Hardy","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Emma Hardy","109978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778130","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-02","<p>It is not departmental policy to provide published documents in any language other than English or, when conducting public business in Wales, Welsh.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-11-02T15:31:49.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778130/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778130/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778130/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-26","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 24 October 2017 to Question 107854, on radicalism, whether the information referred to has been made available in languages other than English.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","110000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778131","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-01","<p>We have been contacted by thirty two local authorities and that seven of these are in the process of providing more detail after initial conversations. It is a matter for local authorities to communicate with their residents what work is being proposed, and as such I cannot release the details of specific local authorities.</p><p>We have been clear that we expect building owners to fund fire safety measures, but councils should contact us if they have any concerns about funding fire safety works. Where works are necessary to ensure the fire safety of a building, we will ensure that lack of financial resources will not prevent them going ahead.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-01T17:29:38.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778131/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778131/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778131/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778131/answer/previousversion/19114","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-26","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to his oral contribution of 5 September 2017, Official Report, column 76, on Grenfell Tower, if he will publish details of the local authorities that have contacted his Department on funding for remedial work.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","110017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778132","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-01","<p>The Government’s consultation,<em> Tackling unfair practices in the leasehold market</em>, considered a number of issues within the leasehold sector including the sale of new built leasehold houses, and onerous ground rents. The consultation also sought views on what further areas of leasehold reform should be prioritised and why.</p><p>The public consultation, which closed on 19 September, received around 6,000 replies. We are carefully analysing the responses, and will issue the Government response in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-01T16:29:20.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778132/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778132/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778132/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-26","Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to bring forward legislative proposals to ensure that freeholders offer leaseholders the first option to purchase that freehold; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Emma Hardy","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Emma Hardy","109990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778133","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-03","<p>We warmly welcome Facebook’s digital safety ambassador scheme, in partnership with the Diana award and Childnet International which aims to provide anti-bullying training for one young person in each UK school. This scheme is a private initiative. The Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport will not be making any evaluation or producing any sponsorship material for the scheme.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","109807","2017-11-03T09:06:33.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778133/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778133/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778133/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-26","Internet: Bullying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps her Department is taking to evaluate the impact, effectiveness and sustainability of the anti-bullying training that Facebook is planning to fund.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","109803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778134","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-03","<p>We warmly welcome Facebook’s digital safety ambassador scheme, in partnership with the Diana award and Childnet International which aims to provide anti-bullying training for one young person in each UK school. This scheme is a private initiative. The Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport will not be making any evaluation or producing any sponsorship material for the scheme.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","109803","2017-11-03T09:06:33.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778134/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778134/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778134/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-26","Internet: Bullying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what branding or other promotional material indicating Facebook's sponsorship will be visible on any of the materials used in pursuit of the Internet Safety Strategy.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","109807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778135","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-02","<p>Tourism as a whole contributed £62.4bn to the economy in 2015. We cannot make an estimate into the contribution of licensed hospitality to the UK economy as we do not hold information on businesses which are specifically licensed versus those that are not.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2017-11-02T11:23:38.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778135/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778135/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778135/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-26","Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate her Department has made of the contribution of the licensed hospitality industry to the UK tourism economy.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","109819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778136","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-03","<p>Resourcing is part of regular discussions with all of our Arm’s Length Bodies.</p><p>In March 2017 I announced a Tailored Review of UK Anti-Doping (UKAD). The Review is considering UKAD’s efficiency, effectiveness and governance; and how it is preparing for the future. The Tailored Review will be published before the end of 2017.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Sporting Future, the government’s sport strategy, made a commitment to ensure that UKAD continues to be funded at the levels needed for it to further enhance its strong reputation and to protect its funding in real terms throughout the current Spending Review period. This is reflected in its Spending Review settlement.</p><p> </p><p>The UK Government remains fully committed to combating doping in sport and protecting the integrity of sport.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","109723","2017-11-03T13:03:08.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778136/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778136/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778136/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-26","UK Anti-doping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions she has had with UK Anti-Doping on the adequacy of its resources.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","109831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778137","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-03","<p>The FA, like all sports bodies in receipt of public funding, is now required to comply with the highest standards of sports governance as set out in Sport England and UK Sport's A Code for Sports Governance. This includes having at least 30 per cent gender diversity on boards, acting in an open and transparent way and making progress on BAME representation in sports administration. All funded bodies have until the 31 October to provide evidence of how they are making progress towards meeting the requirements in the Code. Sport England and UK Sport will be reviewing this evidence, and will continue to be rigorous in their monitoring of on-going compliance.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-11-03T13:16:29.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778137/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778137/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778137/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-26","Football: Governing Bodies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effect of the recent FA governance reforms in addressing the lack of BAME representation in football governance.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","109832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778138","Department for International Trade","false","2017-11-03","<p>Neither the Department for International Trade (DIT) nor the Office for National Statistics (ONS) breaks down the level of foreign direct investment into the licensed hospitality industry.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-11-03T12:23:57.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778138/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778138/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778138/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-26","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what recent estimate his Department has made of trends in the level of foreign direct investment into the licensed hospitality industry in the UK.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","109818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778139","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>The programme to deliver the Fleet Solid Support ships entered the Assessment Phase in April 2016. Current activity is focused on developing the technical specification for the ships and confirmation of the vessels' capability requirements.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:06:30.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778139/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778139/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778139/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Warships: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made on procuring fleet support ships for the Royal Fleet Auxiliary; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","109855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778140","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>Following on from Sir John Parker's trade union engagement prior to publishing his independent report, we have continued to keep the trade unions involved. Representatives from the Confederation of Shipbuilding and Engineering Unions (CSEU) and GMB have attended Industry stakeholder events in relation to the National Shipbuilding Strategy. We also undertook a briefing on the strategy followed by a question and answer session at the CSEU Maritime Forum on 13 February 2017. We will continue to engage with the trade unions as we implement the strategy.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:08:37.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778140/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778140/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778140/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many meetings have taken place between trades union representatives and his Department on the national shipbuilding strategy; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","109853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778141","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>As set out in the National Shipbuilding Strategy, future procurement of ships by the Ministry of Defence will be by competition.</p><p>All Royal Navy warships (destroyers, frigates and aircraft carriers) will continue to have a UK-owned design, and will be built and integrated in the UK. Warship build will be via competition between UK shipyards.</p><p>All other naval ships should be subject to open competition, provided that there are no compelling national security reasons to constrain a particular procurement to national providers. Integration of sensitive UK-specific systems will be done in the UK, where possible after competition between UK providers.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:00:58.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778141/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778141/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778141/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Warships: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what criteria are used to establish whether a contract for naval ships should be advertised and such ships procured by  international rather than national competition; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","109854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778142","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Ministry of Defence is committed to helping the UK defence sector grow and compete successfully; our expenditure with UK industry and commerce was £18.7 billion in 2015-16 and directly supports over 121,000 jobs in every nation and region of the United Kingdom. We will shortly publish our refreshed defence industrial policy which will set out the further steps we are taking to achieve our national security objectives in defence procurement, including to promote prosperity.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:04:20.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778142/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778142/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778142/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to ensure that UK defence procurement supports UK industrial growth; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","109808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778143","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Ministry of Defence welcomes inward investment in the UK supply chain, and works closely with colleagues in Government and with key international suppliers to encourage this. Since 2012, we have seen £3.2 billion of inward investment in the UK defence sector.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:02:12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778143/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778143/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to ensure that UK defence procurement promotes inward investment.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","109809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778144","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Ministry of Defence has measures in place to identify and, where necessary, take action to protect those aspects of capability which are essential to the UK's freedom of action and operational advantage on national security grounds. We are adopting a more vigilant and systematic approach to implementing this, notably in relation to industry's supply chains.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:02:45.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778144/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778144/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778144/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of current UK defence procurement plans in protecting and maintaining sovereign defence capabilities.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","109810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778145","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>As we consider our future requirements, the Ministry of Defence is analysing aspects of the UK military aerospace sector with other Government Departments and UK industry to understand longer-term options for international partnering, industry's appetite to invest, adjacent civil investment and overall affordability.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:03:29.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778145/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778145/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to ensure that UK defence procurements sustain the UK aerospace industry.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","109811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778146","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>The North West of the UK has a strong defence and aerospace manufacturing capability, including for the Eurofighter Typhoon and the F-35 Lightning II. Neither programme is affected by the UK leaving the EU, as they are governed by other arrangements.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:07:59.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778146/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778146/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-26","Aerospace Industry and Defence: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress his Department has made on its assessment of the implications for defence and aerospace manufacturing capability in the North West of the UK leaving the EU; and what the timetable is for completion of that assessment.","false","Biography information for Mike Amesbury","Weaver Vale","Mike Amesbury","109935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778147","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>Forecasted expenditure on Advanced Learner Loans is agreed with HM Treasury on an annual basis. This takes into account historic trends of take-up and any policy changes that are likely to have an impact on future demand.</p><p> </p><p>To date, in each year that Advanced Learner loans have been available, funding has been available to meet the demand from learners.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-10-31T17:16:42.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778147/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778147/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778147/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent discussions she has had with HM Treasury on whether her Department can retain for 2018-19 loans funding allocations for further education learners not taken up in 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778148","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Student Loans Company figures show that the take-up of Advanced Learner Loans by those aged 24 and over was lower in the 2016/17 academic year than it was in 2015/16, by around 8,000.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is examining the reasons for this trend and, with its delivery partners, will continue to provide support to colleges and training providers to improve awareness and understanding of Advanced Learner Loans.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-10-31T17:09:40.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778148/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778148/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of trends in the number of applications from learners aged over 24 for advanced learner loans in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778149","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) decided not to announce a loans provider expansion exercise earlier in 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Following consultation with the Association of Colleges and the Association and Employment and Learning Providers, the ESFA published criteria against which providers could apply for a loans facility in June 2017. The criteria is set out in the Advanced Learner Loans Funding and Performance Management Rules 2017/18.</p><p> </p><p>Learners can obtain an Advanced Learner Loan to support study at over 700 providers.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-10-31T17:14:46.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778149/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778149/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778149/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent discussions she has had with stakeholders on requirements on new further education provider entrants who wish to gain access to further education loans.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778150","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Institute for Apprenticeships is an independent body with responsibility for the development and approval of apprenticeship standards. I have therefore asked the Institute to write to the Rt hon. Member for Blackpool South directly responding to the question about apprentices currently employed by the Institute for Apprenticeships.</p><p> </p><p>A copy of that response will be placed in the Libraries of both Houses when it is available.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-10-31T17:10:55.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778150/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778150/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Institute for Apprenticeships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many apprentices are currently employed by the Institute for Apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778151","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Department recognises that there is a continued need to support colleges and training providers to ensure all potential learners are supported in their awareness and understanding of Advanced Learner Loans. We will continue to encourage colleges and training providers in their outreach activity.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-10-31T17:12:42.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778151/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778151/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to raise the number of applications for further education loans.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778152","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Adult Education Budget (AEB) is not allocated to specific regions. The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) allocates AEB to individual providers, who under the current freedoms and flexibility policy are able to use their funds to support any English learner.</p><p> </p><p>The published allocations can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sfa-funding-allocations-to-training-providers-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sfa-funding-allocations-to-training-providers-2016-to-2017</a>.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-10-31T17:19:29.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778152/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778152/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Adult Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the adult education budget is in each region of England for the current financial year.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","109944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778153","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>The subject content for GCSE and A-level PE was revised in 2015 to address concerns that the previous GCSE and A level courses were not of comparable rigor to other subjects, did not provide suitable progression and had led to inequalities in assessment.</p><p> </p><p>As part of these revisions, the activity list was reviewed to ensure that all activities could be assessed reliably, were of comparable demand amongst pupils, and were manageable for schools to assess. The inclusion or non-inclusion of sports does not represent a view on the legitimacy or value of the activity.</p><p> </p><p>The government will review the activity list in autumn 2018, following the first examinations next summer. We will agree this process with the exam boards and announce details closer to the time.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","109942","2017-10-31T17:33:20.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778153/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778153/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Physical Education: GCE A-level","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, for what reasons speed skating was not included as one of the options available in A-level PE courses for the current academic year.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","109945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778154","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>The subject content for GCSE and A-level PE was revised in 2015 to address concerns that the previous GCSE and A level courses were not of comparable rigor to other subjects, did not provide suitable progression and had led to inequalities in assessment.</p><p> </p><p>As part of these revisions, the activity list was reviewed to ensure that all activities could be assessed reliably, were of comparable demand amongst pupils, and were manageable for schools to assess. The inclusion or non-inclusion of sports does not represent a view on the legitimacy or value of the activity.</p><p> </p><p>The government will review the activity list in autumn 2018, following the first examinations next summer. We will agree this process with the exam boards and announce details closer to the time.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","109945","2017-10-31T17:33:20.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778154/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778154/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-26","Physical Education: GCE A-level","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will reverse the decision not to include speed skating as an option available in A-level PE for the current academic year.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","109942"
