"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778235","Home Office","false","2017-11-07","<p>Home Office Retention and Disposal Standards for corporate information are published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/home-office-retention-and-disposal-standards/what-to-keep-home-office-guide-to-managing-information" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/home-office-retention-and-disposal-standards/what-to-keep-home-office-guide-to-managing-information</a></p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-07T10:28:55.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778235/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778235/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-26","British Nationality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for how many years UK Visas and Immigration maintains records of applications for citizenship.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","109953"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778236","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-14","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-11-14T11:16:51.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778236/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778236/answer","PQ109954.pdf","PQ109954.pdf","UKSA response","UKSA response","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778236/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-26","Domicil","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether he maintains a record of the number of British citizens domiciled in the UK.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","109954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778237","Home Office","false","2017-11-07","<p>A person will usually be able to demonstrate they are a British citizen through presentation of a British passport or certificate of entitlement to the right of abode.</p><p> </p><p>When any question arises as to whether a person is a British citizen or not, the person seeking to establish a claim, must obtain the necessary information or documents themselves.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-07T10:28:39.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778237/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778237/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-26","British Nationality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what procedures exist to determine whether a person is a British citizen if their citizenship is challenged or questioned.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","109952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778238","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-02","<p>Online TV channels licensed by Ofcom must comply with robust rules in the Ofcom Broadcasting Code on harmful or offensive content. Video-on-demand services within UK jurisdiction are subject to higher level rules which focus on harmful material, for example prohibiting incitement to hatred. More widely, as part of the work on the Digital Charter, the government is considering a range of options to counter internet harms. This includes an Internet Safety Strategy, published on 11 October, which considers the responsibilities of companies to their users, the use of technical solutions to prevent online harms and government’s role in supporting users.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-11-02T14:02:28.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778238/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778238/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-26","Video On Demand: Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps the Government is taking to protect people from offensive and defamatory online broadcasting content.","false","Biography information for Alex Chalk","Cheltenham","Alex Chalk","110025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778239","Home Office","false","2017-11-01","<p>Over 200 unaccompanied children have arrived in the UK under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016 and transfers are ongoing.</p><p>The Government is fully committed to delivering our commitment to transfer the specified number of 480 children under section 67. We are working very closely with Member States, as well as the UN High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), the International Organization for Migration (IOM) and NGO partners to identify and transfer children to the UK in line with each individual Member State’s national laws.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-01T17:16:09.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778239/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778239/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-26","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what progress she has made on granting asylum to unaccompanied child refugees in Europe under the Dubs scheme.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","110028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778240","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-06","<p>The animal and plant health conditions applicable to trade between the UK and the EU after the UK leaves the EU will be subject to negotiation. The outcome of these negotiations will influence what form of official controls will be required for trade with the EU in future, including at the UK border. Like all Government departments, Defra is working on preparations for a range of scenarios to deliver a smooth departure from the EU.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-06T14:26:05.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778240/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778240/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-26","Food: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether his Department has allocated funding for the planning and construction of laboratories to inspect meat and plant products at the Dover entrance to the Channel Tunnel in the event that the UK leaves the customs union.","false","Biography information for Mr Chris Leslie","Nottingham East","Mr Chris Leslie","109999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778241","Home Office","false","2017-11-07","<p>All non EEA nationals visiting the UK, including those visiting as religious workers to preach or do pastoral work, are subject to the Immigration Rules, available at (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/immigration-rules/immigration-rules-appendix-v-visitor-rules" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/immigration-rules/immigration-rules-appendix-v-visitor-rules</a> )</p><p>If they do access NHS services, then they will usually be charged. The policy for charging visitors to the UK is the responsibility of the Department of Health. Further information is available at <a href="https://www.nhs.uk/NHSEngland/AboutNHSservices/uk-visitors/visiting-england/Pages/visitors-from-outside-the-eea.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.nhs.uk/NHSEngland/AboutNHSservices/uk-visitors/visiting-england/Pages/visitors-from-outside-the-eea.aspx</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-07T16:19:10.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778241/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778241/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-26","Immigrants: Missionaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the Government's policy is on access for those visiting the UK with missionary status to the NHS.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","109872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778242","Home Office","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Board of the Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority (GLAA) is constituted under The Gangmasters (Licensing Authority) Regulations 2015. Recruitment to the Board follows a fair and open process in line with the Government’s code of practice on public appointments.</p><p>Anyone with relevant experience and ability to contribute to the GLAA Board is able to apply to recruitment rounds.</p><p>The Home Secretary has not discussed the effectiveness of the GLAA Board with trade union representatives.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","109890 ; 109891","2017-10-31T15:30:24.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778242/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778242/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-26","Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reasons the board of the Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority includes no members with recent trade union experience.","false","Biography information for Ellie Reeves","Lewisham West and Penge","Ellie Reeves","109892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778243","Home Office","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Board of the Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority (GLAA) is constituted under The Gangmasters (Licensing Authority) Regulations 2015. Recruitment to the Board follows a fair and open process in line with the Government’s code of practice on public appointments.</p><p>Anyone with relevant experience and ability to contribute to the GLAA Board is able to apply to recruitment rounds.</p><p>The Home Secretary has not discussed the effectiveness of the GLAA Board with trade union representatives.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","109891 ; 109892","2017-10-31T15:30:24.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778243/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778243/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-26","Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether trade union experience is considered desirable in recruitment of members of the Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority board; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ellie Reeves","Lewisham West and Penge","Ellie Reeves","109890"
