td><td><p>21</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>40</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>21</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Grand Total</strong></p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>146</p></td><td><p>102</p></td><td><p>107</p></td><td><p>365</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","109895","2017-10-31T16:21:04.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778294/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778294/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778294/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-26","Road Works: Casualties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many people working on the motorway network have been killed or seriously injured in road traffic incidents in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mike Amesbury","Weaver Vale","Mike Amesbury","109894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778295","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-01","<p>Although no formal discussions have been held, my Department continues to work closely with international partners on security standards.</p><p> </p><p>We look forward to achieving the return of flights once we can be assured that the necessary security environment can be sustained.</p><p> </p><p>It is the responsibility for each Government to determine their own advice on where it is safe for their citizens or carriers to fly.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-11-01T14:08:33.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778295/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778295/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778295/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-26","Air Routes: Egypt","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with his European counterparts on the resumption of flights to Sharm el-Sheikh in Egypt; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","109801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778296","Wales Office","false","2017-11-02","<p>Leaving the EU presents a major opportunity for Welsh and wider UK agriculture and we are working towards achieving the best possible deal for the agricultural industry across the UK. We want to secure a deep and comprehensive Free Trade Agreement as an alternative to membership of the Single Market, which preserves our access to EU markets for red meat, including Welsh lamb, and all agricultural products.</p><p> </p><p>The Office of the Secretary of State for Wales will continue to work with other Government departments including the Department for Exiting the European Union, directly with farmers and farming industry representatives, and Welsh and local Government to support the Welsh economy and promote a prosperous Wales within a strong United Kingdom after we leave the EU.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-11-02T13:11:36.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778296/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778296/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-10-26","Sheep Meat: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what discussion he has had with his (a) Cabinet colleagues and (b) counterpart in the Welsh Government on the effect of leaving the EU without a deal on the export of Welsh lamb to Europe.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","109789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778297","Wales Office","false","2017-11-02","<p>I hold regular discussions with Cabinet colleagues and the Welsh Government. Both Government and independent research has identified that zero hours contracts are an important part of a flexible, modern labour market. However, the Government shares the concerns regarding job security which is why the Prime Minister asked Matthew Taylor to carry out an independent review of employment practices. The review was published on 11th July and we have committed to respond fully in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-11-02T13:12:57.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778297/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778297/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-10-26","Zero Hours Contracts: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what discussions he has had with (a) Cabinet colleagues and (b) the Welsh Government on the use of zero hours contracts in Wales.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","109791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778298","Wales Office","false","2017-11-01","<p>The Wales Office does not employ staff directly as the Ministry of Justice is the employer. There are no non-UK EU nationals currently assigned to the department.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-11-01T13:43:36.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778298/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778298/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-10-26","Wales Office: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many non-UK EU nationals are employed by his Department.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","110005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778299","Wales Office","false","2017-11-02","<p>The port at Holyhead is vital to the economy of north Wales, and acts as an important link between the Republic of Ireland and the UK. A number of UK Government ministers, including the Minister for Security and I, have visited Holyhead to discuss the impact of EU Exit on the port. The UK Government Minister for Wales has also met with Irish Ferries.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to ensuring that withdrawal from the EU is a successful and smooth process for all parts of the UK, and we are conscious that a significant proportion of the traffic at some ports is not currently subject to customs controls. We want to ensure that traffic continues to flow freely at all UK ports and airports, including Holyhead, and we will seek to ensure that customs arrangements and mechanisms are as frictionless as possible, and that trade fluidity is maintained. Officials in the Wales Office and colleagues across Government are working with port operators and other stakeholders in Wales to support the smooth and orderly implementation of these new arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>Responsibility for roads in Wales is devolved to the National Assembly for Wales and the Welsh Government.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-11-02T15:11:27.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778299/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778299/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-10-26","Holyhead Port: Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of introducing customs checks at Holyhead Port on congestion on the A55.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","110026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778300","Women and Equalities","false","2017-10-31","<p>We launched a national survey on 23 July to ask lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender (LGBT) people living in the UK about their experiences of using public services, and about any experiences of discrimination that they may have faced throughout their lives.</p><p> </p><p>The survey closed on 15 October. We received more than 100,000 responses, making this one of the largest ever surveys of LGBT people in the world. We will analyse the results and use them to inform the Government’s policy on LGBT equality. We will publish our findings when this analysis has been completed.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-10-31T17:57:03.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778300/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778300/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-10-26","LGBT People: Public Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what progress the Government is making towards its goal of seeking the views of LGBT people in the UK on public services.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","109847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778301","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-31","<p>As location is stipulated in contracts for DWP staff, a change of location due to Building for our Future impacts would be considered a change to a colleague’s contract.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-10-31T10:46:14.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778301/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778301/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-26","Jobcentres: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 25 October 2017 to Question 108098, on jobcentres: Glasgow, whether his Department plans for staff working in Shettleston, Easterhouse, Bridgeton and Parkhead Jobcentres to have changes made to their employment contracts.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","109858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778302","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-03","<p>The Department no longer holds financial details for the campaign in question. However, people were notified through leaflets, an extensive advertising campaign was carried out, and later individual letters were posted out. For example, throughout this period the Department has been providing individuals with their most up-to-date State Pension age when they have requested a Pension statement. Between April 2000 and the end of July 2017, the Department issued more than 18 million personalised State Pension statements to people who requested them (either online or by telephone or post; and based on both old and new State Pension rules). We continue to encourage people to request a personalised State Pension Statement as part of our on-going communications.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-11-03T12:30:01.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778302/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778302/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-26","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 24 October 2017 to Question 108665, on state retirement pensions: females, how much was spent from the public purse on that extensive advertising campaign; and how that funding was spent by method of advertising.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","109823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778303","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-31","<p>There is no data broken down by area or region.</p><p> </p><p>However, data published on 2 October 2017 shows that, nationally, 81% of new full service claims received their first payment in full and on time. Across the whole of Universal Credit 92% of all households received full payment on time. The published data can be found here.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-payment-timeliness-january-to-june-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-payment-timeliness-january-to-june-2017</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-10-31T17:24:15.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778303/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778303/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 25 October 2017 to Question 108094, on universal credit: Glasgow East, what the longest length of time in days was that a universal credit applicant has waited for their initial payment to date.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","109859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778304","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-31","<p>This information is not collated centrally and could only be obtained at a disproportionate cost.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-10-31T10:44:35.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778304/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778304/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-26","Independent Living Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many former recipients of financial support from the Independent Living Fund in England received (a) improved or equal financial support or (b) reduced such package from local authorities administering the successor scheme.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","109857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778305","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-01","<p>On 27th October 2017, the Independent Case Examiner's Office had 230 complaints about Department for Work and Pensions Service Providers awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-11-01T15:56:20.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778305/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/778305/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-26","Department for Work and Pensions: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many of his Department's service providers' complaints are awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager at the Independent Case Examiner's Office.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","109796"
