"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777555","Home Office","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Government is committed to strengthening the UK's response to bribery, corruption, money laundering, fraud and other forms of economic crime. The Government is continuing to review options to improve the effectiveness of the UK's response to economic crime, and any measures resulting from this work will be announced in due course.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford","HL2555","2017-11-07T17:00:26.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777555/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777555/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-25","Fraud","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether the findings of their internal economic crime review will be made public; and if so, when.","false","Biography information for Baroness Stern",,"Baroness Stern","HL2554"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777556","Home Office","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Government is committed to strengthening the UK's response to bribery, corruption, money laundering, fraud and other forms of economic crime. The Government is continuing to review options to improve the effectiveness of the UK's response to economic crime, and any measures resulting from this work will be announced in due course.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford","HL2554","2017-11-07T17:00:26.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777556/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777556/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-25","Serious Fraud Office","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they have any plans to combine the Serious Fraud Office with any other law enforcement agencies.","false","Biography information for Baroness Stern",,"Baroness Stern","HL2555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777557","Home Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>Subject to Parliamentary time being available, we are aiming to fully commence the provisions relating to unexplained wealth orders by the end of this financial year.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-11-06T17:45:47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777557/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777557/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-25","Unexplained Wealth Orders","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government when they expect section 1 of the Criminal Finances Act 2017 to come into force.","false","Biography information for Baroness Stern",,"Baroness Stern","HL2556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777559","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>The government is working on a new Anti-Corruption Strategy which will be published in due course.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2017-11-06T12:40:40.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777559/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777559/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777559/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-25","Corruption","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the answer by Lord Young of Cookham on 10 July (HL Deb, col 1080), when they intend to publish the UK anti-corruption strategy.","false","Biography information for Baroness Stern",,"Baroness Stern","HL2557"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777560","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>A decision on the anti-corruption champion appointment will be made in due course.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2017-11-06T12:39:38.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777560/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777560/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777560/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-25","Corruption","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government when they intend to appoint a new anti-corruption champion; and whether the champion will be a Cabinet-level position.","false","Biography information for Baroness Stern",,"Baroness Stern","HL2558"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777561","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Department for Transport carries out regular assessments of aviation security at all last points of departure airports to the UK from Egypt. The Government works closely with international partners, including airlines, airports and the Egyptian Government, on security standards. Global aviation security arrangements are kept under constant review. It is the responsibility for each Government to determine their own advice on where it is safe for their citizens or carriers to fly.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg",,"2017-11-07T12:01:31.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777561/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777561/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777561/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-25","Aviation: Egypt","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they have reviewed the ban on direct flights between the UK and Sharm el Sheikh, in the light of such flights being available from other European states, including Italy, Germany, and Belgium.","false","Biography information for Lord Stone of Blackheath",,"Lord Stone of Blackheath","HL2559"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777563","Department for Education","false","2017-11-08","<p>Decisions on pay ranges and allowances are based on recommendations by the School Teachers’ Review Body, the independent body that advises on teachers’ pay and conditions.</p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton",,"2017-11-08T16:28:31.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777563/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777563/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777563/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Teachers: London Allowance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government who is responsible for deciding the level of London allowances for teachers.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL2560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777564","Department for Education","false","2017-11-08","<p>Data on the number of children educated at home are not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>National statistics on the number of children being taught at unregistered schools are not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton",,"2017-11-08T13:35:20.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777564/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777564/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777564/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Education","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of (1) how many children are taught at home, and (2) how many children are taught in unregistered schools.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL2561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777565","Department for Education","false","2017-11-08","<p>The requirements on parents who educate children at home are contained in Section 7 of the Education Act 1996: these are that a child of compulsory school age receives an efficient full-time education suitable to his or her age, ability and aptitudes, and any special educational needs. There is no legal requirement that children educated at home are taught about the Fundamental British Values. A curriculum for a home-educated child which directly contradicted the Fundamental British Values might be deemed not suitable; that would be for the relevant local council to decide.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has established a joint team with Ofsted and given them additional resources to step up investigations in to unregistered schools and to work with us to take whatever action is required, including closing the school or working with the police and Crown Prosecution Service as necessary‎.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton",,"2017-11-08T14:00:43.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777565/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777565/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777565/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","National Identity: Education","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to ensure that children taught at home or in unregistered schools meet the requirements that children are taught British values.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL2562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777566","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-08","<p>Estimates of the number of new homes built in Cornwall and Devon are published by the Department as part of ‘House building; new build dwellings in England’. The number of new homes built, in Cornwall and Devon since 2010/11, is shown in the table below.</p><p><strong>Table 1. House building; new build dwellings completed.</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017-18 (Q1 only)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total </strong> <strong>(to June 2017)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cornwall</p></td><td><p>1,450</p></td><td><p>1,820</p></td><td><p>1,680</p></td><td><p>1,430</p></td><td><p>1,880</p></td><td><p>1,760</p></td><td><p>1,750</p></td><td><p>520</p></td><td><p>12,300</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Devon</p></td><td><p>1,870</p></td><td><p>2,220</p></td><td><p>1,770</p></td><td><p>2,840</p></td><td><p>3,030</p></td><td><p>3,110</p></td><td><p>3,340</p></td><td><p>920</p></td><td><p>19,100</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>A more complete picture of housing supply (including conversions and change of use) is provided by the ‘net additional dwelling’ statistics. The number of net additional dwellings delivered, in Cornwall and Devon since 2010/11, is shown in the table below.</p><p><strong>Table 2. Housing Supply; net additional dwellings.</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total </strong> <strong>(to 2015-16)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cornwall</p></td><td><p>2,390</p></td><td><p>2,380</p></td><td><p>2,280</p></td><td><p>2,030</p></td><td><p>2,700</p></td><td><p>2,600</p></td><td><p>14,380</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Devon</p></td><td><p>2,650</p></td><td><p>2,360</p></td><td><p>2,260</p></td><td><p>3,340</p></td><td><p>3,910</p></td><td><p>3,940</p></td><td><p>18,550</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2017-11-08T16:30:25.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777566/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777566/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777566/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-25","Housing: South West","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many new homes have been built in (1) Cornwall, and (2) Devon, in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Goss Moor",,"Lord Taylor of Goss Moor","HL2563"
